{"article_id":"ZOp94Z59c8aFqq0W","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"You can ' t exactly force friends , neighbors or strangers to wear a face covering","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"to slow the spread of coronavirus ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"but experts prescribe a few approaches","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"to help nudge them in the right direction","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"- and keep yourself safe .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"COVID-19 primarily spreads from person to person through respiratory droplets from coughing , sneezing and talking ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"including by asymptomatic and \" pre-symptomatic \" individuals .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"In a reversal from its earlier guidance , the agency recommended in April","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that Americans wear cloth face coverings","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"while in public places","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that make physical distance difficult to maintain .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"A number of states and businesses also now require mask-wearing in some capacity .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Surveys suggest","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"that many people are complying with such directives :","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"More than two-thirds of respondents to a mid-May HuffPost/YouGov poll , for example , said","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"they either always or mostly wore a face covering","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"while in public and close to other people .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Some 83 % said","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"they did not view that act as a sign of weakness ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and 69 % said","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"they saw it as a sign of respectfulness .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"But viral incidents of mask resistance have cropped up around the country :","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"A video last month showed a Colorado Costco COST , +1.34 % employee","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"bouncing a non-mask-wearing customer","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"whose defense was that he \" woke up in a free country . \"","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"\" A video last month showed a Colorado Costco employee","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"bouncing a non-mask wearing customer","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"whose defense was that he ' woke up in a free country . ' \"","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Some protesters have reportedly tried to co-opt disability and medical privacy laws","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"to exempt themselves from wearing masks .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"A May dispute over a Flint , Mich. , Family Dollar DLTR , -1.38 % customer","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"not wearing a mask","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"resulted in a security guard ' s death .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Meanwhile , President Trump said at a Ford F , +6.13 % plant last month","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"that he had declined to wear a mask in public","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"because he \" didn ' t want to give the press the pleasure","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"of seeing it , \"","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"after wearing one during an earlier part of his tour .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Last month , Mike Pence acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"that he made a mistake","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"by visiting patients at the Mayo Clinic","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"without a mask ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"while health-care workers said","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"management and staff at the Mayo Clinic have serious soul-searching to do .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"If you live with a mask nonconformist ,","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"or you ' ve encountered one at your job or neighborhood grocery store ,","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"here are some expert-endorsed strategies","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"for persuading them","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"while protecting your own health and safety :","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"\" The first thing is to be a role model ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and to wear your mask","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"and to wear it properly , \"","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"said Zeke Emanuel , a University of Pennsylvania oncologist and bioethicist","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"who helped craft the Affordable Care Act","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"and now advises Joe Biden ' s presidential campaign .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"\" It ' s important for average people ;","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"it ' s especially important for celebrities , political leaders , business leaders. \"","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Setting this example helps establish social norms and expectations ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"he told .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"David Abrams , a professor of social and behavioral science at the NYU School of Global Public Health , said","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"that each individual","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"who wore a mask","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"was \" helping contribute to the new normal. \"","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"\" Observational learning is extremely powerful ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"and therefore","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"whether it ' s one-on-one or a few people or someone in a leadership position ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"anybody","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"wearing a mask","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"is strongly helping other people to wear one , \"","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"You can also offer positive reinforcement to people","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"who do wear masks .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"\" How about saying ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"' Thank you for wearing a mask , '","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"or ' I appreciate","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"that you ' re wearing a mask ' ? \"","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"suggested Gretchen Chapman , a professor of psychology at Carnegie Mellon University .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"Cite a rule or policy","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"to make it less personal","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"If a customer at your workplace is flouting the rules ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"try deferring to an external authority ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"said Emma Frances Bloomfield , an assistant professor of communication studies at the University of Nevada , Las Vegas","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"who studies scientific skepticism and misinformation .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Explain","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"that your workplace mandates mask-wearing for everybody","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"and it ' s your job to enforce the rules ,","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"she said ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"\" so it ' s less about attacking them and their specific decision . \"","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"It can also help to direct the person to resources , like extra masks ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Whole Foods AMZN ,","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"-0.71 % , for example , announced in late April","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that it would offer free disposable masks to customers .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Chapman said","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"if a student came to her office hours","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"without a face covering ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"she would appeal to Carnegie Mellon ' s guidance","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"that everyone on campus wear one","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"- that way , the student would be less likely to take it personally .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"\" Even if that university rule weren ' t there ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"I could say ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"' I have a personal rule","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"that I ' ll only meet with people","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"when we ' re all wearing masks ,","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"so could you put on a mask ? ' \"","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"Publicizing the rules ahead of time isn ' t a bad idea ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"she added .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"Bloomfield advised against engaging with strangers","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"who aren ' t wearing masks in a store or outside .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"\" If you don ' t have any power or authority in a situation ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"people probably aren ' t going to react kindly or openly to being policed by others , \"","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"\" Direct confrontation with people","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"you don ' t know","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"is not a good idea. \"","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"( This person might also not be wearing a mask for reasons","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"you don ' t know about ,","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"like a disability . )","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"If you do engage with someone ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"use \" I \" messages rather than \" you \" messages ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"ask questions ,","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"study the person ' s nonverbal behavior for emotional cues ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"and try to empathize with their reason","depth":15},{"id":126,"text":"for not wearing a mask ,","depth":15},{"id":127,"text":"Abrams said .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Stay calm , firm and neutral ,","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"he added ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"and \" be curious about them","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"rather than impose your will on them . \"","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"\" Attacking someone , criticizing them","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"for not doing the right thing","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"- that almost never works , \"","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Emanuel added .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"Friends and family members will be easier to talk to","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"since you share a personal connection ,","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Bloomfield said .","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"If you know the person ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"\" you could certainly appeal to common values and experiences , \"","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"she added .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"\" Perhaps you know people in common","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"who are particularly at risk","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"for contracting the disease .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"\" It ' s important to \" make it easy for people to do the right thing , \"","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"said Emanuel .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"\" In an ideal world , we would have lots of masks","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"that are free or very cheap , \"","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"On an individual level , increasing ease might look like carrying around extra masks","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"to give to people","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"who need them ,","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"or sewing or buying masks for your relatives or roommates .","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"Keep masks near the door","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"so they ' re easy to grab","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"when your family goes out .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"In the workplace ,","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"he added ,","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"you could \" encourage","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"- maybe even demand -","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"that your employer provide suitable masks. \"","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"\" That ' s what it means to operate a safe work environment these days , \"","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"Emanuel said .","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"You might be able to cultivate norms about mask-wearing in your workplace or organization ,","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"Chapman said ,","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"including by having a discussion beforehand","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"in which everyone signs on to the idea","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"of wearing a mask .","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"If you ' re meeting up with a friend for a socially distanced coffee ,","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"Bloomfield said ,","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"set ground rules ahead of time","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"and plan for both of you to wear face coverings .","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"And","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"if you live with someone ,","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"lay down rules and expectations for your communal living space .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"\" If you live in the same household ,","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"it ' s not just your decisions affecting your own personal space","depth":14},{"id":179,"text":"- it ' s affecting everyone ' s space , \"","depth":14},{"id":180,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"If the person isn ' t sold on wearing a mask ,","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"Bloomfield suggested","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"asking them to just go along with it :","depth":11},{"id":184,"text":"\" Maybe I ' m overreacting ,","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"but humor me","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"- I ' d rather be safe","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"than sorry. \"","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"\" You ' re asking the person to compromise for your concerns and well-being ,","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"even if it ' s not something","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"they ' re particularly concerned about ,","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"because you want to maintain the friendship or the relationship , \"","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"\" To a large extent , you can control what situation you ' re in , \"","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"Chapman said .","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"\" You can leave the store","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"or walk farther away from the person .","depth":12},{"id":197,"text":"You could make up whatever excuse","depth":13},{"id":198,"text":"you need","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"to walk away from the situation . \"","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"\" If you don ' t have authority over the space ,","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"we can ' t really tell people what they can and can not do , \"","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"Bloomfield said .","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"\" It ' s best to just control your own well-being and what you feel comfortable with ,","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"and create the rules for your own spaces","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"as best you can . \"","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"Consider ,","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"Chapman added ,","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"that there are all sorts of situations","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"not involving COVID-19","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"in which people have different approaches to risky situations .","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"\" You might be somewhat judgmental of people","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"who binge drink","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"or don ' t wear seat belts all the time ,","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"but you ' re not going to be mortal enemies with them","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"because of that -","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"you ' re going to try to protect yourself , \"","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"she said .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":435,"left":222,"right":434,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":222,"left":219,"right":221,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":219,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":2,"right":220,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":434,"left":261,"right":433,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":261,"left":238,"right":260,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":238,"left":224,"right":237,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":224,"left":223,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity